Responsibilities include but are not limited to: 
Manage and prepare US international tax calculations, including E&P, Subpart F inclusions, GILTI, BEAT, FDII, and foreign tax credits 
Manage and prepare Forms 5471, 8858, 8865, 1118 and other international tax reporting/disclosures for the US federal income tax return ensuring timely and accurate tax return filings 
Assisting with the preparation of aspects of the US GAAP tax accounting of non-US operations for the quarterly and annual income tax provisions 
Reviewing foreign tax packages and working with foreign tax teams 
Support continuous improvements in tax provision and compliance processes by challenging the status quo to optimize efficiency, including using transformation tools robotic processes. Interfacing with the IRS, state revenue agencies, and outside advisors to resolve tax controversies 
Carry out tax technical research and understand impact of proposed tax legislation and prepare technical memos and documentation 
Your Qualifications include, but not limited to: 
5+ years of large corporate or Big Four tax experience in U.S. international tax 
Graduate degree or CPA preferred 
Knowledge of ONESOURCE and advance use of Excel 
Experience with SAP, Blackline, Power BI, and Alteryx is a plus. 
Tax controversy experience is preferred 
Well organized and focused on structure in the compliance process 
Able to work independently and identify solutions to challenging issues in a fast- paced, business focused environment 
Strong focus on working as a team and contributing to staff development 
Detailed oriented with the ability to multi-task 
A focus on value creation and a passion for tax 
